-- BHP, Billabong, Discovery, Mirabela: Australian, N.Z. Equities
-- B y   D a v i d   F i c k l i n g
-- 2012-01-23T05:49:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/australian-n-z-equities-downer-discovery-range-resources.html
Australia ’s  S&P/ASX 200 Index  fell
0.3 percent to 4,225.10 at the close of trading in Sydney. New
Zealand’s NZX 50 Index gained 0.6 percent to 3,295.02 in
Wellington.  The following were among the most active shares in the
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names.  Mining companies: Stocks in the sector dropped after the
 London Metal Exchange Index (LMEX)  of six industrial commodities
including copper and aluminum fell 1.1 percent on Jan. 20. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BHP AU), the world’s biggest miner, declined 0.6
percent to A$37.24. Fortescue Metals Group Ltd. (FMG AU) shed
3.7 percent to A$5.  Discovery Metals Ltd. (DOW)   jumped 8.4 percent to
A$1.615, its highest level since listing in 2003, after the
Australian Financial Review newspaper reported that the copper
and nickel producer may be a takeover target for OZ Minerals
Ltd.  Billabong International Ltd. (BBG)  , the world’s second-
largest listed surf-wear company, climbed the most in a month
with a 6.4 percent increase to A$1.985.  Mirabela Nickel Ltd. (MBN)   was the worst performer on
the benchmark index, dropping 6.5 percent to A$1.215 after
fourth-quarter results from its Brazilian operations showed an
11 percent increase in production costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
